  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What happens if you overdose on Naproxen?",
  "response": "Overdosing on naproxen can lead to serious health issues. Here are some potential effects and symptoms of a naproxen overdose:\n\n### Symptoms of Naproxen Overdose\n- **Stomach Pain**: Severe abdominal pain or discomfort.\n- **Nausea and Vomiting**: Persistent nausea and vomiting.\n- **Drowsiness**: Feeling excessively sleepy or lethargic.\n- **Headache**: Intense headaches.\n- **Dizziness or Lightheadedness**: Feeling faint or unsteady.\n- **Breathing Difficulties**: Shortness of breath or difficulty breathing.\n- **Confusion**: Mental confusion or disorientation.\n- **Seizures**: In severe cases, seizures may occur.\n- **Unconsciousness**: Loss of consciousness in extreme cases.\n\n### Potential Complications\n- **Gastrointestinal Bleeding**: Naproxen can irritate the stomach lining, and an overdose can lead to bleeding.\n- **Kidney Damage**: High doses of naproxen can impair kidney function.\n- **Liver Damage**: Overdose can cause liver toxicity.\n- **Heart Problems**: Increased risk of heart attack or stroke.\n\n### What to Do\nIf you suspect a naproxen overdose, seek immediate medical attention. Call emergency services or go to the nearest emergency room. It's important to inform healthcare providers about the amount of naproxen ingested and the time of ingestion.\n\n### Prevention\n- **Follow Dosage Instructions**: Always adhere to the prescribed dosage and duration.\n- **Consult Healthcare Providers**: Discuss any concerns or side effects with a doctor or pharmacist.\n- **Keep Out of Reach**: Store naproxen and other medications out of reach of children and individuals who might misuse them.\n\nUnderstanding the risks and taking preventive measures can help avoid the severe consequences of a naproxen overdose.",
